data.title: DVIDS
data.text:
Freedom Watch Update - July 27

Deployed service members may not have all the comforts of home; but most troops still have easy access to essentials like fuel and water. Senior Airman Monique Benedict shows us what it takes to make sure warriors in remote locations have the bare necessities and for Harrier Jets flying missions over Southern Afghanistan, its up to Marine Aerial Refuelers with Transportation Squadron 152 to keep them in the air. Soundbite includes SSG. Joseph Turner - 2668 Transportation Company and Capt. Mark Bock - Co-pilot. Produced by SrA. Monique Benedict and Amn. Jimmy Moreland. Hosted by SSgt. Josh Rosales, Afghanistan. Also available in High Definition.

07/27/2012

Freedom Watch Update - May 18

U.S. soldiers with the 425th ID complete an air assault with their Afghan counterparts in Paktia Province, Afghanistan and took the time to share how their making a difference in the district and SSgt. Josh Rosales finds a female service member who has made her way to the front lines to help clear one of the biggest threats to service members in Afghanistan. Soundbites include SGT. Joshua Ethridge - Squad Leader; SGT. Jason Childers - Squad Leader and LT. Brittany Hine - Platoon Leader 584th MAC. Produced by SSgt. Josh Rosales. Hosted by MC2. Zulema Sotelo. Also available in High Definition.

05/18/2012

Freedom Watch Update - April 27

Service members support the mission all across Afghanistan and when they're injured no matter the time or location members of Task Force Talon are there to support them and a key Air Force leader pays a visit to Airmen at Kandahar Airfield to thank them for their service and to discuss the challenges the Air Force will overcome in the future. Soundbites include CPT. Robert Grumbo - Flight Surgeon and Gen. Norton Schwartz - Chief of Staff U.S. Air Force. Produced by SPC. Fred Brown and TSgt. Burt Traynor. Hosted by MC2. Zulema Sotelo. Also available in High Definition.

04/27/2012

Freedom Watch Update - Feb 3

This edition features stories about how promotions are a significant event in anyone's career but for one Master Sergeant it was an added bonus to have his stripes pinned on by the Chief Master Sergeant of the Air Force. Soundbites include SMSGT Timothy Tart - Task Force Paladin and CMSgt. James A. Roy - CMSAF. Produced by SPC. David Innes, Afghanistan. Another story about how one maintenance team travels around Afghanistan bringing Football to remote operating bases across the country. Soundbites include SMSgt. Don Gurganus - AFN Theater Planner. Produced by SSgt. Shannon Ofiara. Hosted by LCpl. Christofer Baines. Also available in High Definition.

02/03/2012

Freedom Watch Update - Jan 26

This edition features a story about Joint combat outpost Shir Khan is a new addition to the Afghanistan, Tajikistan border. The 40th Engineer Battalion built it to support Afghan border police training and to secure this vital supply route between the two countries. During the first few months of construction, the Soldiers who live and work here had to eat M-R-E's. until Cpl John smart arrived and set up his field kitchen. There are sound bites from Spc. Jerry Howard, Combat Engineer, Sgt. John Smart, Food Service Specialist, and Capt. Nicholas Barry, Company Commander, Alpha Company 40th Engineer Battalion. Produced by PO2 Brandon Shelander. Also available in High Definition.

01/26/2012

Freedom Watch Update - Jan 25

This edition features a stories about how over the years, our military has invented numerous useful items and tools...from night vision and G.P.S to the jet pack and silly putty. Petty Officer Kyle Jackson brings us the story on one unit at Bagram Airbase, Afghanistan whose creative ideas help war fighters in the field and a story about how Combat Medics prepare for the battle field in Kabul, Afghanistan. Soundbites include Jim Granitzki - RDECOM Engineer and Dr. Majib Mujib - KNMH Physician. Produced by MC3 Kyle Jackson and SSG. Danielle Washington. Hosted by SrA. Alina Richard. Also available in High Definition.

01/25/2012

Freedom Watch Update - Jan. 4

This edition features stories about how service members deployed to the front lines often find themselves taking the full force of whatever Mother Nature decides to throw at them on any given day. Lance Corporal Christofer Baines introduces us to a small group of Airmen who travel Afghanistan to bring much needed shelter to the Troops and their equipment. Soundbite includes SSgt. Michael Henderson. Produced by LCpl. Christofer Baines. Also a story about base security with soldiers from the 1st Battalion 179 Infantry. Soundbite includes SFC. Michael Rhoades - 45th Infantry Brigade Combat Team. Produced by Spc. Shanna Gantz. Hosted by SrA Alina Richard. Also available in High Definition.

01/04/2012

Freedom Watch Update - Dec 15

This edition features stories about how American soldiers are passing on their knowledge to local Afghan Forces in preparation for the transition of authority to the Afghan government. Marine Corporal Tia Nagle was with the group during a patrol and a story about how Combat Medics are passing along skills of their own that will help save lives on the battlefield. Soundbites include 1LT Daniel Smith - US Army Border Patrol and CPT. Robert Hughs - Administrator. Produced by Cpl. Tia Nagle and Spc. Crystal Madriz. Hosted by SSgt. Melissa Hay. Also available in High Definition.

12/15/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Dec 14

This edition features stories about how the Combined Joint Operation Are Afghanistan chapter of the Sergeant Audie Murphy Club welcomed 16 new soldiers to its ranks on Kandahar Airfield, Afghanistan. The Sergeant Audie Murphy Club was created to inspire, motivate and develop the best leaders possible in the U.S. Army and a story about how deployment for the soldiers of the 2-2 Infantry Battalion draws to a close. Petty Officer Erick Holmes met up with the battalion commander to discuss the achievements of his soldiers. Soundbites include LTC. Alan Streeter - Commander, 2-2 Infantry, Hometown: Bucksport, ME. Produced by PO2 Erick Holmes and Produced by LCpl. Christofer Baines. Also available in High Definition.

12/14/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Nov 24

This edition features a story about a soldier getting his toenail removed. Medical care at FOB Connolly. Medics at Forward Operating Base Connolly, Afghanistan, keep the soldiers in the fight. One soldier has had his own fight with his foot and another story about how the 35th Commandant of the Marine Corps, Gen. James F. Amos and Sgt. Maj. of the Marine Corps, Sgt. Maj. Michael Barrett visited service members at Kandahar Airfield, Afghanistan. Soundbite includes SSG. Joshua Carrasco -... read more

This edition features a story about a soldier getting his toenail removed. Medical care at FOB Connolly. Medics at Forward Operating Base Connolly, Afghanistan, keep the soldiers in the fight. One soldier has had his own fight with his foot and another story about how the 35th Commandant of the Marine Corps, Gen. James F. Amos and Sgt. Maj. of the Marine Corps, Sgt. Maj. Michael Barrett visited service members at Kandahar Airfield, Afghanistan. Soundbite includes SSG. Joshua Carrasco - U.S. Army, Medic, Spc. Robert Smith - U.S. Army, Patient, 35th Commandant of the Marine Corps, Gen. James F. Amos and Sgt. Maj. of the Marine Corps, Sgt. Maj. Michael Barrett. Produced by SSgt. Chad Usher. Hosted by SSgt. Melissa Hay. Also available in High Definition. show less

11/24/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Nov 2

This edition features a story about how Afghan Airmen and Soldiers secure a local area in Spin Boldak, Afghanistan and a story about how Marine Corps General John R. Allen Commander of NATO and International Security Assistance Force troops in Afghanistan sent 20 runners in Kabul on there way for the Marine Corps Marathon or MCM Forward by blowing the start whistle. The 26.2 mile run allows runners that participate in the run to test their endurance in unfriendly terrain. Soundbites include Benjamin Ranta - Event Coodinator, COL. Gary Johnson - Commander, 504th Battlefield Intelligence Group. Produced by SSgt. Jose Rodriquez and hosted by SSgt. Melissa Hay. Also available in High Definition.

11/02/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Sep 29

This edition features stories about how U.S. Ambassador Ryan Crocker talks about a naturalization ceremony that took place at Bagram Airfield, Afghanistan. Sep. 28, 2011 and how applying medical treatment to troops on the battlefield needs to happen fast. The time it takes to translate to an Afghan Soldier on proper techniques can mean the difference between an injury and a casualty. Marine Sgt. Todd Crowell was with some Army Medics who help Afghans help each other. Soundbite includes Sgt. Anthony Merino - NCOIC FOB Kushmond Aid Station, Afghanistan. Produced by Sgt. Todd Crowell. Hosted by Sgt. Jenn Casanova. Also available in High Definition.

09/29/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Sep 28

This edition features stories about how even though these soldiers are downrange the need for training doesn't stop. The combat life saver training course is designed to keep troops ability to save lives at its peak. The training team has a variety of real combat like scenarios. The training provides each service member with the tools to be a combat medic. Practice builds confidence and with that confidence everyone can make a difference. Also when soldiers patrol outside the wire in... read more

This edition features stories about how even though these soldiers are downrange the need for training doesn't stop. The combat life saver training course is designed to keep troops ability to save lives at its peak. The training team has a variety of real combat like scenarios. The training provides each service member with the tools to be a combat medic. Practice builds confidence and with that confidence everyone can make a difference. Also when soldiers patrol outside the wire in Afghanistan, they sometimes run into trouble. Marine Sgt. Todd Crowell was with a group of artillery men who help those ground units with fire from above. Soundbite includes 1LT. James Treharne - Platoon Leader, 2nd Plt. Alpha Battery and Dontray David - Training & Development Specialist. Produced by Sgt. Todd Crowell, PO3 Tristan Miller and hosted by Sgt. Jenn Casanova. show less

09/28/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Sep 14

This edition features a story about how giving the country of Afghanistan back into the hands of the Afghan National Army requires that troops make sure that things are as safe as they can be. Marine Sgt. Todd Crowell traveled with a platoon from Task Force Blackhawk to scan the outlying are to make sure that it was as safe as it could be. Produced by Sgt. Todd Crowell

09/14/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Sep 1

This edition features a story about there are dozens of flights in the AOR everyday and Bagram Airfield is the busiest terminal in Afghanistan. The passenger terminal however is not capable of housing the thousands of people traveling to and from Bagram, but all that is about to change. Transitioning from the old terminal to the new one, customers can enjoy more spacious waiting areas, air conditioning and an overall better experience while traveling threw the new Bagram PX. Soundbite includes Brig. Gen. Darryl Roberson - Commander, 455th AEW. Produced by A1C Marshall Hunsaker.

09/01/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Aug 31

This edition features a story about how the rank Corporal is the first rank in the Marine Corps as an NCO and the course is of ten times the first experience as a leader. The Cpl. Course graduates can now take what they've learned and put it to use, training new Marines and influencing the old. Soundbites include Cpl. Adam Conley - Student and Sgt. Kyle Husted - Instructor. Produced by A1C. Marshall Hunsaker. Afghanistan.

08/31/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Aug. 12

Bagram Airfield is known for a few things like being one of the largest bases in Afghanistan, but it is seldom known for the great food that's prepared for thousands of people everyday. Petty Officer 3rd Class Tristan Miller takes us to the Aviation Dining Facility for a taste of Bagram. Includes sound bite from Sgt. Scott Richards, First Cook.

The demand for air mobility support is rising as U.S. military forces press further into isolated areas. With a higher ops tempo for air drops, comes a greater need to have someone on the ground to make sure things go smoothly. Air Force Staff Sgt. Josie Anders has more. Anchored by Airman 1st Class Marshall Hunsaker.

08/12/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Aug 11

This edition features stories about how proper evidence is needed to prove someone's innocence or guilt. AF Staff Sgt. Chad Usher went to Torkham Gate on the Afghanistan Pakistan border where Soldiers are logging biometrics of people crossing the border to acquire the evidence and local Afghans in the Paktika Province will begin to see some new faces. Marine Cpl. Kevin Beebe takes us to a ceremony that bids farewell to one task force and welcomes another. Soundbites include 1st Lt. Brad Rigg - Biometrics Collection Specialist - TF Biometrics, FOB Torkham and Col. Edward Bohnemann - Commander, 172nd Seperate Infantry Brigade. Stories produced by Staff Sgt. Chad Usher and Cpl. Kevin Beebe. Hosted by Airman 1st Class Marshall Hunsaker.

08/10/2011

Freedom Watch Update - May 11

This edition features a story about to fly a U-2, Pilots have to be the best of the best, they must be able to fly at altitudes around 70,000 feet for several hours, putting their bodies to the test. Senior Airman Michael Cowley introduces us to a pilot from Southwest Asia that knows the feeling all to well. Sound bites includes U-2 Pilot - 99th Expeditionary Reconnaissance Squadron. Produced by Senior Airman Michael Cowley and hosted by Lance Cpl. Benjamin Harris

05/11/2011

Freedom Watch Update - April 11

U.S. service members continue to work with their Afghan counterparts in training their military to prepare for the security transitions in July. Not only does this mean training Afghans to be able to fight insurgents in their country, but also teaching them how to train future generations of Afghan soldiers to fight. Spc. Adam Dineen shows us how one unit is getting the Afghan National Army in Paktika province to train it's own. Includes soundbites from 2nd Lt. Ubaid Urhaman and 1st Sgt. Wali, both with the Afghan National Army.

04/08/2011

Freedom Watch Update - Dec 10

This edition features a stories about how British and NATO Ambassadors met with Afghan officials and and the Nangarhar Provincial Reconstruction team in Nangarhar Province, Afghanistan to discuss the areas security and welfare and Package about how U.S. and Coalition Forces strive to win the battle of hearts and minds as they rebuild Afghanistan, but a big part of this process lies with the local people. Staff Sgt. Yoshi Shinzato tells us how U.S. and Coalition Forces are empowering the... read more

This edition features a stories about how British and NATO Ambassadors met with Afghan officials and and the Nangarhar Provincial Reconstruction team in Nangarhar Province, Afghanistan to discuss the areas security and welfare and Package about how U.S. and Coalition Forces strive to win the battle of hearts and minds as they rebuild Afghanistan, but a big part of this process lies with the local people. Staff Sgt. Yoshi Shinzato tells us how U.S. and Coalition Forces are empowering the Afghan people. Sound bites include Brig. Gen. Warren Plupps - Deputy Commander of Combined Joint Task Force 101, Park Hee-Yoon Korean Ambassador, Abdul Saboor Azia Construction Teacher and Muhammad Sahim Construction Student. Hosted by Staff Sgt. Jessica King. show less

12/10/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Dec 1

This edition features a stories on how International Security Assistance Forces have one less Haqqani Leader to worry about in Khost Province, Afghanistan and Coalition Forces in Afghanistan are working hard to fight the information war. Air Force Staff Sgt. James Zannetti takes us to Parwan Province where they're teaching young Afghan Journalists to be first with the truth. Sound bites include Ms. Mahtab Farid, U.S. Department of State Public Diplomacy Officer, Regional Command East,... read more

This edition features a stories on how International Security Assistance Forces have one less Haqqani Leader to worry about in Khost Province, Afghanistan and Coalition Forces in Afghanistan are working hard to fight the information war. Air Force Staff Sgt. James Zannetti takes us to Parwan Province where they're teaching young Afghan Journalists to be first with the truth. Sound bites include Ms. Mahtab Farid, U.S. Department of State Public Diplomacy Officer, Regional Command East, Combined Joint Task Force 101, Hometown: Washington, D.C. and Army Master Sgt. David Gillespie, Regional Command East Regional Communications Center, Information Operations Non Commissioned Officer in Charge (NCOIC), Hometown: Clarksville, Tenn. Hosted by Lance Cpl. Benjamin Harris. show less

12/01/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Nov 22

This edition features stories on This edition features a story on how an Afghan organization is educating women in Ghazni Province, Aghanistan with the help of U.S. service members and forty years ago, Afghanistan was the leading exporter of dried fruits and nuts around the world, with the help of Coalition Forces and partners, like the United States Department of Agriculture, the country is entering the twenty-first century. Air Force Staff Sgt. Will Bracy brings you the story of A U.S.D.A. Representative who found a way for Afghanistan to once again be a worldwide exporter of dried goods. Sound bites include Caroline Clarin, PRT Paktika Agricultural Adviser from Fort Atkinson, Wis. Hosted by Petty Officer 1st Class Dustin Diaz.

11/22/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Oct 29

This edition features a stories on how members of the Afghan National Army graduated from a new training course in Kabul Province, Afghanistan and how in General David Petraeus' recent Counterinsurgency Guidance, one of his building blocks for success is "fighting the information war aggressively." One way that's being accomplished is empowerment of Radio Stations and local Afghan DJ's to bring the airwaves back to Afghanistan. Marine Staff Sgt. Jeremy Vought introduces us to one such Afghan in Logar Province. Sound bite includes "Khosal" - Happy, Unity 94.5 DJ. Hosted by Petty Officer 1st Class Dustin Diaz.

10/29/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Oct 8

This edition features a stories on how Insurgents continue to injure and kill Afghan men, women and children in Afghanistan and The Coalition's largest and busiest logistics base, Bagram Air Field, supports Operations in Afghanistan, though it is taxed. Coalition officials are bridging gaps and relieving stress on Bagram by adding strategic landing strips that can handle the Air Force's strategic heavy lifter, the C-17. Marine Staff Sgt. Jeremy Vought reports from Logar Province,... read more

This edition features a stories on how Insurgents continue to injure and kill Afghan men, women and children in Afghanistan and The Coalition's largest and busiest logistics base, Bagram Air Field, supports Operations in Afghanistan, though it is taxed. Coalition officials are bridging gaps and relieving stress on Bagram by adding strategic landing strips that can handle the Air Force's strategic heavy lifter, the C-17. Marine Staff Sgt. Jeremy Vought reports from Logar Province, Afghanistan where Globemasters are landing for the first time. Sound bites include Maj. Ashley Thames, Brigade Aviation Officer, 173rd Airborne Brigade Combat Team, from Manchester, Tenn., Staff Sgt. Dave Cygon, FOB Shank Material Handling Equipment NCOIC, 9-19th Inland Cargo Transfer Co., Michigan and Capt. Jeremy Brockman, C-17 pilot, 817th Expeditionary Airlift Squadron. Hosted by Petty Officer 1st Class Dustin Diaz. show less

10/08/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Oct 1

This edition features storie on how Afghan and Coalition Forces captured IED makers in Khost and Paktika Provinces, Afghanistan in late September and Forward Operating Bases and Combat Outposts receive supplies by air, but for smaller locations, convoys are necessary to move building and personal supplies. Air Force Staff Sgt. Alana Ingram met some of the Soldiers who do this on a daily basis in Afghanistan. Sound bites include Staff Sgt. Cliff Hecker, Personal Security Detail NCOIC, from W. Va. and 1st Lt. Mark Butcher, Personal Security Detail Engineer, from W. Va. Hosted by Staff Sgt. Alana Ingram.

10/01/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Sept. 24

This edition features a story on when Afghan and Coalition Forces secure areas that were once Insurgent strongholds, it provides an opportunity for development in Afghanistan and Forward Surgical Teams are spread throughout Forward Operating Bases in Afghanistan. They are the first line of Hospital care service members and locals receive during an emergency. Air Force Staff Sgt. Alana Ingram takes us to Forward Operating Base Sharana as their FST brings in a pair of casualties. Sound bites include Maj. Sidney Collins, FST Surgeon, Staff Sgt. Frederick Kesler, Combat Medic, and Spc. Timothy Black, Medic. Hosted by Petty Officer 1st Class Dustin Diaz.

09/24/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Sep 15

This edition features stories on how more and more, Afghans in Afghanistan are taking a leading role in running their own country. Senior Airman Chris Pyles reports on some of the country's newest guardians and how one of the key points in counterinsurgency operations is legitimizing local government throughout Afghanistan. Senior Airman Chris Pyles takes us to a village in Wardak Province where the locals serve as the example for what COIN is all about. Sound bite includes Staff Sgt. William Alford Task Force Brawler Squad Leader. Hosted by Senior Airman Chris Pyles.

09/15/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Aug 30

This edition features stories on how Afghan Forces are taking the lead in defending their Nation from insurgent fighters with in their own country and abroad and on how the U.S. run Detention Facility in Parwan Province, Afghanistan has ended its silence on what they do and how they do it. Petty Officer 1st Class Dustin Diaz went inside and brings us the story. Sound bite includes Brig. Gen. Mandi Murray, 46th Military Police Commander. Hosted by Petty Officer 1st Class Dustin Diaz.

08/30/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Aug 27

This edition features stories about how the Afghan Government want to welcome Insurgents to a peaceful way of life, and some former fighters are doing just that and a joint study by several health organizations revealed 82 percent of people diagnosed with Post Traumatic Stress Disorder partnered with a trained psychiatric service dog will have fewer symptoms. Air Force Staff Sgt. Alana Ingram reports on a special deployment of PTSD fighters in Afghanistan. Sound bite includes Capt. Theresa Schillreff, Occupational Therapist. Hosted by Petty Officer 1st Class Dustin Diaz.

08/27/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Aug 25

This edition features a story on how International Forces are sending a clear message to all would be insurgents: If you fight us, you will lose. Air Force Staff Sgt. Alana Ingram reports on a terrorist cell leader who ignored that warning and when a service member enlists in the U.S. Military they promise to defend the constitution of the United States with their life. Senior Airman Barbara Patton reports from Panjshir, Province, Afghanistan on Troops who honor their fallen brothers and sisters with a hike in their memory. Hosted by Staff Sgt. Alana Ingram.

08/25/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Aug 13

This edition features stories on how the Insurgents continue to kill civilians and the body count is getting disturbingly high and security in Wardak Province has improved over the past year. Karl W. Eikenberry, U.S. Ambassador to Afghanistan, speaks to a crowd of Afghan civilians and coalition forces, Aug. 12, 2010 during a shura in Wardak Province with Gen. David Petraeus and the governor of Wardak. The Taliban fires an RPG at the meeting to try to disrupt it. The shura continued. Sound bite includes Gen. David Petraeus. Hosted by Petty Officer 1st Class Dustin Diaz.

08/13/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Aug 11

This edition features stories on how the Terrorists sink to new depths every day to terrorize Afghan civilians and in July the Craig Joint Theater Hospital on Bagram Air Field, Afghanistan cared for nearly 3,000 patients, both U.S. and local nationals. U.S. Doctors treat patients for everything from bumps and bruises to severe head trauma. The staff works around the clock to provide care for the injured and comfort their family. Hosted by Petty Officer 1st Class Dustin Diaz.

08/11/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Aug. 5

This edition features stories on the terrorist activities of the Haqqani network experiencing a setback when Afghan and coalition forces detained known and suspected insurgents in the Khost province, Afghanistan and the maintainers, pilots and electronic countermeasures officers of Marine Electronic Attack Squadron 2, known as the Death Jesters, providing electronic tech support to all coalition forces in Afghanistan and their use of the EA-6B Prowlers, the primary tactical electronic jamming aircraft used by most U.S. military branches. Hosted by Petty Officer 1st Class Dustin Diaz. Includes soundbites from Lance Cpl. Kevin Davis - Prowler crew chief and Maj. Roderick Capili - electronic countermeasure officer.

08/05/2010

Freedom Watch Update - July 22

This edition features stories on how the Taliban lost another safe haven and staging area in Kunar Province, Afghanistan thanks to Afghan and NATO Forces and some of the outlying bases in Afghanistan are pretty remote and it can take days to get a flight into one of them. One soldier makes sure people and equipment can get to his area of operation. Sound bite includes Staff Sgt. Wayne Schill. Hosted by Staff Sgt. Jeremy Vought.

07/22/2010

Freedom Watch Update - July 20

This edition features stories on how coalition forces have documented an increase in insurgents of using Mosques, using them to train, fight and equip and how security and governance are two of the key mission strategies of American Forces serving in Afghanistan as part of Operation Enduring Freedom and Soldiers who make those strategies part of their daily mission. Sound bites include 1st Lt. Patrick Roush from Fort Campbell, KY. Hosted by Staff Sgt. Alana Ingram.

07/20/2010

Freedom Watch Update - July 1

This edition features a stories on how the U.S. Military shows the Afghan people that they are here to help by putting construction and development at the top of the priority list in Afghanistan. The Army Corps of Engineers helps in Gardez District and about when U.S. Forces begin to draw back in 2011, they will start to transition Bagram Air Field, Afghanistan over to the Afghan people, by providing the base with equipment that is reliable, sturdy and can put out the amount of power needed. Hosted by Petty Officer 3rd Class Cody Boyd.

07/01/2010

Freedom Watch Update - June 10

This edition features stories on an attack at a wedding part in Kandahar province, Afghanistan in which several people were killed or injured and an Afghan radio station on Forward Operating Base Sharana, Afghanistan broadcasting information to the Afghan people to keep them informed of the truth and to combat misinformation spread by the Taliban. Hosted by Senior Airman Jay Hernandez. Includes soundbites from Karimullah, Radio in the Box DJ, and Army 1st Lt. RJ Peek, an information officer.

06/10/2010

Freedom Watch Update - June 3

This edition features a story on an Afghan International Security Force in Khost Province Afghanistan and how they captured several Haqqani Network Commanders and other Militants and how Afghanistan's Provincial Governors aren't elected by the people, but appointed by the President and how the new Khost Province Governor is closing the gap between himself and his people. . Hosted by Staff Sgt. Michael Jackson.

06/03/2010

Freedom Watch Update - May 7

This edition features stories on a flood in Herat province, Afghanistan killing at least twenty people and injuring thirty others. Afghan and coalition forces are helping with rescue efforts and an agricultural development team and members of the Afghan National Army reaching out to show a nomadic tribe that the Afghan government cares about them and wants to help provide for their needs. Hosted by Air Force Staff Sgt. Alana Ingram.

05/07/2010

Freedom Watch Update - Jan. 15

This edition features stories on the Kunar provincial governor and the commander of Task Force Warrior visiting three provinces in western part of Kunar province, Afghanistan in an effort to connect the provincial government with district governments and a reconnaissance mission in the Khost province of Afghanistan in which U.S. Soldiers will work alongside Afghan security forces ensuring they will be able to conduct future missions without coalition assistance. Hosted by Senior Airman Jay Hernandez.

01/15/2010
